vectorData.altText: 18. To what cell type do nuclei A belong? Be specific.
That's right!  Ependymal cells are ciliated cuboidal to columnar cells that line free surfaces in CNS (e g. the central canal of spinal cord).
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

ependymal cells =ciliated cuboidal to columnar epithelial cells
line free surfaces within the CNS: the walls of the ventricles (fluid-filled spaces in the brain) and the central canal of the spinal cord
cilia help propel CSF through ventricular system
ependymal cells also cover the blood vessels of the choroid plexus, a brain structure that actively secretes cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) into the ventricles
CSF fills spaces within the CNS (i.e. the ventricles) and around the CNS (i.e the cisterns)
